T1  - Rural-urban migration, urban unemployment and underemployment, and job-search activity in LDCs
AU  - Fields, Gary S.
JO  - Journal of Development Economics
VL  - 2
IS  - 2
SP  - 165
EP  - 187
PY  - 1975
DA  - 1975/06/01/
SN  - 0304-3878
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-3878(75)90014-0
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304387875900140
AB  - This paper analyzes unemployment and underemployment in LDCs within a quantity adjustment framework. Four extensions of the Harris-Todaro model are made, including allowances for more generalized job-search behavior, an urban traditional sector, preferential hiring by educational level, and labor turnover considerations. The result of these modifications is a much lower predicted unemployment rate, which accords more closely with actual observations. Some additional policy implications deriving from the analysis are noted.
